<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>About — A Story, A Key</title>
  <meta name="description" content="About Aashima — the reader, the thinker, the person behind A Story, A Key." />
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Cormorant+Garamond:ital,wght@0,300;0,400;0,600;1,300;1,400&family=DM+Sans:wght@300;400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />

  <style>
    :root {
      --ink:     #1a1814;
      --ink2:    #4a4740;
      --ink3:    #8a8680;
      --paper:   #f7f4ef;
      --paper2:  #efeae2;
      --accent:  #5c3d2e;
      --accent2: #8b5e3c;
      --gold:    #c9a96e;
      --white:   #ffffff;
      --ff-display: 'Cormorant Garamond', Georgia, serif;
      --ff-body:    'DM Sans', system-ui, sans-serif;
    }
    *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
    html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }
    body {
      font-family: var(--ff-body);
      background: var(--paper);
      color: var(--ink);
      font-size: 16px;
      line-height: 1.7;
      overflow-x: hidden;
    }
    a { color: inherit; text-decoration: none; }

    /* ── Nav ── */
    nav {
      position: fixed;
      top: 0; left: 0; right: 0;
      z-index: 100;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: space-between;
      padding: 1.2rem 2.5rem;
      background: rgba(247,244,239,0.92);
      backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
      border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(92,61,46,0.1);
    }
    .nav-logo {
      font-family: var(--ff-display);
      font-size: 1.15rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      letter-spacing: 0.02em;
      color: var(--accent);
    }
    .nav-links {
      display: flex;
      gap: 2rem;
      list-style: none;
      font-size: 0.82rem;
      font-weight: 400;
      letter-spacing: 0.06em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--ink2);
    }
    .nav-links a:hover { color: var(--accent); transition: color 0.2s; }
    .nav-links .active-link { color: var(--accent); font-weight: 500; }

    /* ── Page hero ── */
    .page-hero {
      padding: 10rem 2rem 5rem;
      max-width: 820px;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }
    .eyebrow {
      font-size: 0.72rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.18em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--gold);
      font-weight: 500;
      margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
    }
    .hero-title {
      font-family: var(--ff-display);
      font-size: clamp(2.8rem, 7vw, 5rem);
      font-weight: 300;
      line-height: 1.08;
      color: var(--ink);
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }
    .hero-title em { font-style: italic; color: var(--accent); }

    .hero-intro {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      color: var(--ink2);
      line-height: 1.85;
      max-width: 620px;
      border-left: 2px solid var(--gold);
      padding-left: 1.5rem;
      font-family: var(--ff-display);
      font-style: italic;
      font-weight: 300;
    }

    /* ── Main content ── */
    .about-body {
      max-width: 820px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 0 2rem 6rem;
    }

    /* ── Philosophy section ── */
    .philosophy {
      padding: 4rem 0;
      border-top: 1px solid rgba(92,61,46,0.1);
    }
    .section-label {
      font-size: 0.72rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.18em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--gold);
      font-weight: 500;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }
    .section-title {
      font-family: var(--ff-display);
      font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4vw, 2.6rem);
      font-weight: 300;
      line-height: 1.15;
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }
    .section-title em { font-style: italic; color: var(--accent); }
    .prose {
      font-size: 0.97rem;
      color: var(--ink2);
      line-height: 1.9;
      max-width: 600px;
    }
    .prose + .prose { margin-top: 1.2rem; }

    /* ── What I look for cards ── */
    .lens-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(240px, 1fr));
      gap: 1.25rem;
      margin-top: 2.5rem;
    }
    .lens-card {
      background: var(--white);
      border: 1px solid rgba(92,61,46,0.1);
      border-radius: 2px;
      padding: 1.5rem;
    }
    .lens-icon {
      font-family: var(--ff-display);
      font-size: 1.8rem;
      font-style: italic;
      color: var(--gold);
      line-height: 1;
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    }
    .lens-title {
      font-size: 0.85rem;
      font-weight: 500;
      letter-spacing: 0.06em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--ink);
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }
    .lens-desc {
      font-size: 0.88rem;
      color: var(--ink2);
      line-height: 1.7;
    }

    /* ── Reading in numbers ── */
    .numbers {
      padding: 4rem 0;
      border-top: 1px solid rgba(92,61,46,0.1);
    }
    .numbers-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(160px, 1fr));
      gap: 1.5rem;
      margin-top: 2rem;
    }
    .number-item {
      border-top: 2px solid var(--gold);
      padding-top: 1rem;
    }
    .number-big {
      font-family: var(--ff-display);
      font-size: 3rem;
      font-weight: 300;
      color: var(--accent);
      line-height: 1;
    }
    .number-label {
      font-size: 0.75rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.1em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--ink3);
      margin-top: 0.4rem;
    }

    /* ── Favourite books ── */
    .favourites {
      padding: 4rem 0;
      border-top: 1px solid rgba(92,61,46,0.1);
    }
    .fav-list {
      list-style: none;
      margin-top: 2rem;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0;
    }
    .fav-item {
      display: flex;
      align-items: baseline;
      gap: 1.2rem;
      padding: 1rem 0;
      border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(92,61,46,0.08);
      transition: padding-left 0.2s;
    }
    .fav-item:hover { padding-left: 0.5rem; }
    .fav-num {
      font-family: var(--ff-display);
      font-size: 0.85rem;
      color: var(--gold);
      min-width: 1.5rem;
      font-style: italic;
    }
    .fav-title {
      font-family: var(--ff-display);
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      font-style: italic;
      color: var(--ink);
      flex: 1;
    }
    .fav-author {
      font-size: 0.75rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--ink3);
    }

    /* ── Quote interlude ── */
    .quote-interlude {
      background: var(--ink);
      margin: 0 -2rem;
      padding: 4rem 2rem;
      text-align: center;
    }
    .big-quote {
      font-family: var(--ff-display);
      font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 3.5vw, 2.2rem);
      font-weight: 300;
      font-style: italic;
      color: var(--paper);
      max-width: 580px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      line-height: 1.55;
      position: relative;
      padding: 0 1rem;
    }
    .big-quote::before {
      content: '\201C';
      position: absolute;
      left: -0.5rem;
      top: -1rem;
      font-size: 5rem;
      color: var(--gold);
      opacity: 0.3;
      line-height: 1;
    }
    .big-quote-attr {
      display: block;
      margin-top: 1.2rem;
      font-family: var(--ff-body);
      font-style: normal;
      font-size: 0.75rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.12em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: rgba(247,244,239,0.4);
    }

    /* ── Connect section ── */
    .connect {
      padding: 4rem 0 2rem;
      border-top: 1px solid rgba(92,61,46,0.1);
    }
    .connect-body {
      margin: 1.5rem 0 2rem;
      font-size: 0.97rem;
      color: var(--ink2);
      line-height: 1.85;
      max-width: 520px;
    }
    .email-btn {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.6rem;
      padding: 0.85rem 2rem;
      background: var(--accent);
      color: var(--white);
      border-radius: 2px;
      font-size: 0.82rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.1em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      font-weight: 500;
      transition: background 0.2s;
    }
    .email-btn:hover { background: var(--accent2); }

    /* ── Reveal ── */
    .reveal {
      opacity: 0;
      transform: translateY(20px);
      transition: opacity 0.55s ease, transform 0.55s ease;
    }
    .reveal.in-view { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }

    /* ── Footer ── */
    footer {
      background: var(--ink);
      color: var(--paper);
      padding: 3rem 2rem;
      text-align: center;
    }
    .footer-logo {
      font-family: var(--ff-display);
      font-size: 1.3rem;
      font-style: italic;
      color: var(--gold);
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    }
    .footer-links {
      display: flex;
      gap: 1.5rem;
      justify-content: center;
      list-style: none;
      margin: 1rem 0;
      font-size: 0.78rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.1em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: rgba(247,244,239,0.45);
    }
    .footer-links a:hover { color: var(--gold); transition: color 0.2s; }
    .footer-sub { font-size: 0.8rem; color: rgba(247,244,239,0.3); }

    @media (max-width: 768px) {
      nav { padding: 1rem 1.25rem; }
      .nav-links { display: none; }
      .page-hero { padding: 7rem 1.25rem 3rem; }
      .about-body { padding: 0 1.25rem 4rem; }
      .quote-interlude { margin: 0 -1.25rem; }
      .lens-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .numbers-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <!-- Nav -->
  <nav>
    <a href="index.html" class="nav-logo">A Story, A Key</a>
    <ul class="nav-links">
      <li><a href="index.html#feel">Feel Something</a></li>
      <li><a href="books.html">Books</a></li>
      <li><a href="index.html#dna-teaser">Literary DNA</a></li>
      <li><a href="about.html" class="active-link">About</a></li>
    </ul>
  </nav>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <div class="page-hero reveal">
    <p class="eyebrow">The person behind the pages</p>
    <h1 class="hero-title">I read to understand<br><em>people.</em></h1>
    <p class="hero-intro">
      Books, to me, have always been the most honest version of a person, the author
      at their most unguarded, and the reader at their most open. That's the exchange
      I'm interested in.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Body -->
  <div class="about-body">

    <!-- Philosophy -->
    <div class="philosophy reveal">
      <p class="section-label">Why this site exists</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">Books as <em>mirrors.</em></h2>
      <p class="prose">
        Hi! I am Aashima and I have always been a reader. Not because it was assigned, or because it seemed
        like the right thing to do but because I genuinely cannot understand the world
        without stories. A book is the only place where you get to be inside someone
        else's mind completely. That's extraordinary when you stop to think about it.
      </p>
      <p class="prose">
        My interests sit at the intersection of psychology and literature the way
        characters behave, why they make the choices they do, what their inner lives
        reveal about human nature more broadly. I am less interested in whether a book
        is "well-written" in a technical sense, and more interested in what it
        <em style="font-family: var(--ff-display); color: var(--accent);">does</em>
        to the person reading it.
      </p>
      <p class="prose">
        A Story, A Key is my attempt to build something that lasts — not just a log
        of books I've finished, but a living archive of what they unlocked.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- What I look for -->
    <div class="philosophy reveal">
      <p class="section-label">How I read</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">What I look for in <em>every book.</em></h2>
      <div class="lens-grid">
        <div class="lens-card">
          <div class="lens-icon">ψ</div>
          <div class="lens-title">Psychology</div>
          <div class="lens-desc">Why do the characters do what they do? What are they hiding — from others, from themselves? The best books are case studies in human behaviour.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="lens-card">
          <div class="lens-icon">∿</div>
          <div class="lens-title">Moral complexity</div>
          <div class="lens-desc">I distrust books where right and wrong are obvious. Real life isn't that clean. I want characters who are difficult to judge — because people are.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="lens-card">
          <div class="lens-icon">◎</div>
          <div class="lens-title">The thing beneath</div>
          <div class="lens-desc">Every great book is about something underneath its surface story. A murder mystery about grief. A love story about power. I'm always looking for that layer.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="lens-card">
          <div class="lens-icon">⌘</div>
          <div class="lens-title">What it leaves behind</div>
          <div class="lens-desc">The test I use: what does this book leave in you after you close it? A question, a feeling, a shift in how you see something. That's the only metric that matters.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Numbers -->
    <div class="numbers reveal">
      <p class="section-label">By the numbers</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">The archive, <em>so far.</em></h2>
      <div class="numbers-grid">
        <div class="number-item">
          <div class="number-big">47</div>
          <div class="number-label">Books reviewed</div>
        </div>
        <div class="number-item">
          <div class="number-big">15+</div>
          <div class="number-label">Countries of origin</div>
        </div>
        <div class="number-item">
          <div class="number-big">8</div>
          <div class="number-label">Emotional moods mapped</div>
        </div>
        <div class="number-item">
          <div class="number-big">∞</div>
          <div class="number-label">Still left to read</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Favourites -->
    <div class="favourites reveal">
      <p class="section-label">If you asked me right now</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">Books I keep <em>returning to.</em></h2>
      <ul class="fav-list">
        <li class="fav-item">
          <span class="fav-num">i.</span>
          <span class="fav-title">No Longer Human</span>
          <span class="fav-author">Osamu Dazai</span>
        </li>
        <li class="fav-item">
          <span class="fav-num">ii.</span>
          <span class="fav-title">Crime and Punishment</span>
          <span class="fav-author">Fyodor Dostoevsky</span>
        </li>
        <li class="fav-item">
          <span class="fav-num">iii.</span>
          <span class="fav-title">The Remains of the Day</span>
          <span class="fav-author">Kazuo Ishiguro</span>
        </li>
        <li class="fav-item">
          <span class="fav-num">iv.</span>
          <span class="fav-title">The God of Small Things</span>
          <span class="fav-author">Arundhati Roy</span>
        </li>
        <li class="fav-item">
          <span class="fav-num">v.</span>
          <span class="fav-title">The Bell Jar</span>
          <span class="fav-author">Sylvia Plath</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p style="font-size:0.82rem; color:var(--ink3); margin-top:1.2rem; font-style:italic; font-family:var(--ff-display);">
        Ask me again in six months. The list will be different.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Quote interlude -->
    <div class="quote-interlude reveal">
      <blockquote class="big-quote">
        I have always shook with fright before human beings. Unable as I was to feel
        the least particle of confidence in my ability to speak and act like a human being.
        <span class="big-quote-attr">— Osamu Dazai, No Longer Human</span>
      </blockquote>
    </div>

    <!-- Connect -->
    <div class="connect reveal">
      <p class="section-label">Get in touch</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">Want to <em>talk books?</em></h2>
      <p class="connect-body">
        If a review made you think differently about a book, if you want to recommend
        something, or if you just want to argue about an ending; I am genuinely
        interested. Reach out.
      </p>
      <a href="mailto:astoryakey@gmail.com" class="email-btn">
        ✉ &nbsp; Write to me
      </a>
      <p style="font-size:0.8rem; color:var(--ink3); margin-top:1rem;">
      </p>
    </div>

  </div><!-- end about-body -->

  <!-- Footer -->
  <footer>
    <p class="footer-logo">A Story, A Key</p>
    <ul class="footer-links">
      <li><a href="index.html#feel">Feel Something</a></li>
      <li><a href="books.html">Books</a></li>
      <li><a href="about.html">About</a></li>
    </ul>
    <p class="footer-sub">Built with curiosity by Aashima · 2025</p>
  </footer>

  <script>
    const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
      entries.forEach(e => {
        if (e.isIntersecting) {
          e.target.classList.add('in-view');
          observer.unobserve(e.target);
        }
      });
    }, { threshold: 0.1 });
    document.querySelectorAll('.reveal').forEach(el => observer.observe(el));
  </script>

</body>
</html>
